; MD5 sums of the disk images.
; 6ffa36eb7685265c52ab4487ccfe0b0b  d1.img
; e0fe0b4298df89e6751d53a72f1296dd  d2.img
;
; This disassembly is produced by first dumping the whole CS in DOSBox
; debugger when the interpreter is running and then disassembling the
; binary with ndisasm (shipped with nasm). I have added a few comments
; here and there of course.


;  0x0029  = base of variables
;  0x0036  = var 13
;
;  0x0137  = base of info about LOGIC resources
;  0x0191  = see opcode 4F; maybe logic entry 5A
;  0x0192  = see opcode 4F; maybe logic entry 5A
;  0x0197  = base of info about VIEW resources
;  0x01D3  = base of info about PICTURE resources
;  0x021E  = base of info about SOUND resources
; 
; [0x023E] = number of LOGIC resources in memory
; [0x0240] = number of VIEW resources in memory
; [0x0242] = number of PICTURES resources in memory
; [0x0246] = number of SOUND resources in memory
;
; [0x03C1] = speed
;
; [0x0412] = pointer to base of object structures (entry size is 0x2B)
; [0x0416] = base pointer to item structs (entry size 3, 2=owner [0xF9=EGO])
